Hungary Investigating Mol Chairman About INA, Poslovni Reports

-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 
2011-09-16T05:59:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/hungary-investigating-mol-chairman-about-ina-poslovni-reports.html
Hungarian prosecutors are
investigating Mol Nyrt. Chairman Zsolt Hernadi in connection to
allegations he may have bribed former Croatian premier Ivo Sanader to win control of INA Industrija Nafte d.d. for the
Hungarian refiner, Poslovni Dnevnik said, citing Gabor Ivan,
 Hungary ’s ambassador to  Croatia , in an interview.  “You must know that the Hungarian state prosecutor has
started its own investigation on the issue,” Gabor Ivan,
Hungarian ambassador to Zagreb, said in an interview.  Hungary is cooperating with Croatian authorities in the
investigation, Ivan said, according to the Zagreb-based business
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
